    <h2>About the Music Ministry</h2>
    <p>Welcome to the Music Ministry at Shiloh Missionary Baptist Church... a ministry dedicated to building up the body, sharing the gospel, and worshipping our Lord through the medium fit for the King of Kings! It is an honor to have you visit our site. We have many items of interest. Visit us again soon, as more information and features will be added to this page.</p>
    <h3>General Information</h3>
    <p>he Shiloh Music Ministry is committed to providing vibrant and diverse music for our worshippers, with the focus on glorifying God and edifying the Body. Read below how you can serve the Lord through music at Shiloh.</p>
    <h3>Divisions in the Music Ministry</h3>
    <h4>Adult Choir</h4>
    <p>The primary function of the choir is to lead in the morning corporate worship experience as well as ministering throughout the service as appropriate. Our first priority is to worship our Creator in the services as well as in each member's personal life.</p>
    <p>The choir meets on Fridays from 6:45-8:30 PM for rehearsal and prayer. On Sunday morning the choir meets in the Choir lounge for devotion 15 minutes before the 8:00 and 11:00 AM services. You are always welcome to come sit in on rehearsal. For more information call Xavien Phillips at 276-6673.</p>
    <h4>Adult Orchestra</h4>
    <h4>Youth Praise Band</h4>
    <p>The Youth Praise Band consists of youth who are already taking Band in school. These young people have agreed to develop and utilize their talents to glorify God with the goal of supporting worship.</p>
    <h4>Youth Choir</h4>
    <h4>Children's Choir</h4>
    <p>The Shiloh Children's Choir is under the direction of Mrs. Cynthia Hardy, and is for children from Kindergarten to 6th grade. Mrs. Hardy works to provide child-appropriate music that enhances their understanding of worshipping and praising God. The children meet every other week for rehearsal and participate in many other educational opportunities such as: Fundamentals of Music, learning to play recorders, and practicing vocal warm-ups. They also partner with the Shiloh Children's Ministry and participate in many other community and special events throughout the year.</p>
